18 February 2010Following the State of the Nation Address of 11 February 2010, Government will hold Cluster Media Briefings on the implementation of the Programme of Action for 2010. The briefings will take place at the Imbizo Media Centre, 120 Plein Street in Cape Town from 23 February to 11 March 2010.There will be a simultaneous video link up to Room 153, Union Buildings in Pretoria.Briefings schedule:Tuesday, 23 February 201008h30-10h00: Social Protection and Community Development (Chair: Ministers Social Development, Edna Molewa)Monday, 1 March 201009:00-10:30: Infrastructure Development (Chair: Minister of Transport, Sibusiso Ndebele)Tuesday, 2 March 201011:00-13:30: Economic Sectors and Employment (Chair: Minister of Rural Development and Land Reform, Gugile Nkwinti)Wednesday, 3 March 2010 09:00-10:30: Governance and Administration (Chair: Minister of Home Affairs, Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma)Thursday, 4 March 201009:00-10:30: Justice, Crime Prevention and Security (Chair: Minister of Justice, Jeff Radebe)Tuesday, 9 March 2010NB: THIS BRIEFING HAS BEEN POSTPONED UNTIL FURTHER NOTICE11:00-13:30: International Cooperation, Trade &amp; Security (Chair: Minister of Defence and Military Veterans, Lindiwe Sisulu)Wednesday, 10 March 201009:00-10:30: Special media briefing on 2010 Fifa World Cup Preparations (TBC)Thursday, 11 March 201012h00-13h30: Human Development Cluster (Chair: Minister of Basic Education, Angie Motshekga)Thursday, 12 March 201012h00-13h30: International Cooperation, Trade &amp; Security Cluster (Chair: Minister of Defence and Military Veterans, Lindiwe Sisulu)Enquiries Pheliswa Sebati Cell: 082 413 4609Liezil Cerf Cell: 076 778 2380Issued by: Government Communications (GCIS)top